Residents of Atlantis outside Cape Town are demanding urgent intervention at its police station following several incidents of alleged police brutality. eNCA's Monique Mortlock reports. Courtesy of #DStv403 CAPE TOWN - Residents of Atlantis outside Cape Town are demanding urgent intervention at its police station following several incidents of alleged police brutality. READ: Atlantis police officer accused of sexual assault removed In the latest incident, community leaders say officers allegedly manhandled and swore at the woman in front of her 9-year-old child. She was being arrested for contempt of court. READ: Atlantis residents live in fear of the police The Human Rights Commission says it's dealing with more than a dozen cases of police brutality in Atlantis. Watch the video above for more details.